-- SPAIN DAYBOOK: Rajoy in Parliament; May Retail Sales
-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 2012-06-27T03:28:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/spain-daybook-rajoy-in-parliament-may-retail-sales.html
Prime Minister  Mariano Rajoy  and
other members of government answer questions in Parliament. The
national statistics institute INE releases retails sales for
May.  All times in CET (ET+6)  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Question time in Parliament starting from 9 a.m.  GOVERNMENT:
* Regional health chiefs meet Health Minister Ana Mato in Madrid
to discuss budget cuts starting at 5 p.m.  ECONOMY:
* INE releases May retail sales at 9 a.m., previous was -9.8
percent.
* The central government had a budget deficit of 3.41 percent
through May, compared with a 3.5 percent target for the full
year, the budget ministry said yesterday.  EQUITIES:
* Banca Civica yesterday said holders of EU880.2m of preferred
shares, or 97.4%, accepted to swap the notes into subordinated
mandatory convertible bonds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
